Turn on the mircopiHat by connecting it to a laptop through the USB port. Once turned on a white LED will turn on. The HAT will begin to sense the temperature.
When the temperature is very low, no light will be emitted, however once thetemperature reaches 15 degrees, the red light will be emitted from the red LED 
This red light will indicate a low temperature which will be between 15-20 degrees. The normal operating temperature is between 21-59 degrees,and a green light will be emitted from the green LED, 
once the maximum temperature of 60Â°C is reached,a blue light will be emitted from the Blue LED 
